cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a grasp planner for a robotic hand and evaluates it with several robotic hands. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper incorporates local surface structure information to construct feasible and robust grasping poses. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper presents an approach for autonomously generating high-quality grasps. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper may have used machine learning techniques to generate the grasping strategies. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses mean curvature skeletons to segment the object and identify suitable grasp regions.
